The management of University of Benin, Benin City, Edo State has confirmed the date for her 2020/2021 academic session, Post University tertiary matriculation examination, POST-UTME and Post direct entry admission screening exercise. According to the statement signed by the Public Relations Officer, Benedicta Ehanire, Ph.D. and obtained from the University official Facebook handle by DAILY POST on Monday evening, the screening exercise for POST-UTME will commence from 2nd to 12 December 2020 while Post direct entry is billed for 14 to 16 same month. She said the exercise will hold under the supervision of the institution consultancy services across it designated centres in Ogbowo campus. “The exercise has not be postponed, it will hold as scheduled,” she maintained.